CCCCLI. Anno 4. Hampton Episcopi. To J. de Holteby‚ seneschal. Pay Robert, reeve (prepositus) of Northon, 4li. 45. 1od.‚ paid by him to Richard de Button by our order.

CCCCLII. Idus April„ anno 4, (April 13, 1270). Suwell’. To E. de F enton. Pay Hugh de Babington‚ our valet, 270 mares for household expenseS.

CCCCLIII. 18 kal. Maii, anno 4, (April 14, 1270). Schelford. To Clement the sequestrator. Pay our valet, Robert de Ascot', 1oos. from the goods of inte-states for household expenseS.

CCCCLIV. 8 kal. Junii‚ anno 4, (May 25, 1270). London. To E. de Fenton. Pay Reyner de Luk’, or Thomas his partner‚ merchants of Lucca, 200 markS, “ quas ab eisdem Londoniis mutus recepimus ad expensas domus nostrae.”

CCCCLV. 14 kal. Aug„ anno 4, (July 19, 1270). Stibbenh’ prope Londonias (Stepney). To the same. Pay our valet, Richard de Button, 5oli. for household expenseS.

CCCCLVI. 4 non. Junii‚ anno 5, (June 2, 1271). Fo.51. Otingdon. To J., bailiff of Cherch’. Pay Master R. de Fangefosse four score and 15li. 8s. 4d. for household ex enseS.
